content:
Manage Articles and Content with Salesforce Knowledge

Create and manage company information, securely sharing it when needed. Draft, publish, translate, and manage Knowledge articles.

Authoring Actions in Lightning Knowledge:
Use edit, publish, and restore actions to manage articles from the Knowledge home and article record pages.
 
Work with Articles and Translations:
The Article Management tab is your home page for working with articles throughout the publishing cycle as they are created, assigned to collaborators, translated, published, archived, and deleted.

Rich Text Fields in Knowledge Articles:
Use a range of formatting options when creating article content in custom rich text fields.
 
Create and Link to Anchors:
Create anchors within rich text fields so you can link from one place in an article to another.

Smart Links to Salesforce Knowledge Articles:
Link between articles or embed links to articles in external websites and resources, with automatically updated links based on the article channel, version, and URL name.

Salesforce Knowledge Article Versions:
Save older versions of published articles, associating them with cases. Use the Flag as new version checkbox when publishing a new version.
title: Managing Knowledge Content in Service Cloud
